Title: Poison [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poison]

For example, many poisons are important feedstocks (e.g. feeding chickens Arsenic antihelminths
), solvents (e.g. rubbing alcohol, turpentine), cleaners (e.g. bleach, ammonia), coatings (e.g. Arsenic wallpaper
), and so on. Even the toxicity itself sometimes has economic value, when it serves agricultural purposes of weed control and pest control. It further allows better crop production, leading to increase in export volume.
